name: abalone
title: Abalone
description: Dataset for predicting the age of abalone from physical measurements. The age of abalone is determined by cutting the shell through the cone, staining it, and counting the number of rings through a microscope -- a boring and time-consuming task. Other measurements, which are easier to obtain, are used to predict the age.
target_description: Numbe of rings; +1.5 gives the age in years

name: ailerons
title: Ailerons
description: The Ailerons dataset provides flight status attributes of an F16 aircraft, aimed at predicting the control action on its ailerons using regression.
target_description: Control action on the ailerons of the aircraft

name: aquatic_toxicity
title: QSAR Aquatic Toxicity
description: This dataset was used to develop quantitative structure-activity relationship (QSAR) models to predict acute aquatic toxicity towards the fish Pimephales promelas (fathead minnow).
target_description: Concentration that causes death in 50% of test Daphnia Magma over a test duration of 48 hours

name: auto_mpg
title: Auto MPG
description: The auto-mpg dataset contains information about various car attributes, such as cylinders, horsepower, and weight, and aims to predict the miles-per-gallon (mpg) fuel efficiency of the cars. The regression task is to use these attributes to accurately predict the mpg, providing insights into the relationships between car characteristics and fuel efficiency.
target_description: Target: city-cycle fuel consumption in miles per gallon

name: billboard_spotify
title: Billboard Spotify Audio Features
description: This dataset represents a collection of audio features for songs that made their mark on various Billboard charts spanning the years 1961 through 2022. The dataset is formulated as a regression task to predict the "danceability" of a track given other audio features.
target_description: Danceability describes how suitable a track is for dancing based on a combination of musical elements including tempo, rhythm stability, beat strength, and overall regularity. A value of 0.0 is least danceable and 1.0 is most danceable.

name: cancer_mortality
title: Cancer Mortality Rates by U.S. County (2010-2016)
description: This dataset, aggregated from sources like the American Community Survey, clinicaltrials.gov, and cancer.gov, is designed for regression tasks to predict cancer mortality rates in US counties from 2010 to 2016. It incorporates 2013 census data, including county-level features such as population, income, households, and other demographic attributes.
target_description: Dependent variable. Mean per capita (100,000) cancer mortalities from years 2010-2016

name: college_pell_grants
title: College Pell Grant Dataset
description: Modified version for the automl benchmark. Regroups information for about 7800 different US colleges. Including geographical information, stats about the population attending and post graduation career earnings. Dataset is used to predict the percent of students with Pell Grants given various attributes regarding the college and its student population.
target_description: Target variable - percent of undergraduate students awarded Federal Pell Grants

name: computer_activity
title: Computer Activity
description: The Computer Activity dataset captures system metrics from a multi-user Sun Sparcstation 20/712 at 5-second intervals, intended for regression analysis to predict system performance based on varied user tasks.
target_description: Portion of time (%) that cpus run in user mode.

name: diamond_prices
title: Diamond Prices
description: Dataset is based on a case study called "Sarah Gets a Diamond". This case was presented in the first year decision analysis course at Darden School of Business (University of Virginia). The task is to predict the price of a diamond given attributes such as carat weight, cut, color, clarity, polish, symmetry and report (grading agency which reported the qualities of the diamond).

name: energy_efficiency
title: Energy Efficiency
description: The Energy Efficiency dataset consists of 8 features from 768 simulated building shapes in Ecotect, designed for regression tasks to predict both heating and cooling load requirements.

name: fluid_pressure
title: Fluid Dynamics Pressure Estimation Dataset
description: This dataset, inspired by Bernoulli's fluid dynamics principles, is designed for regression tasks to predict fluid pressure based on properties like density, velocity, height, and a celestial body representing gravitational acceleration. It includes missing data points and abstract representations, challenging regression models to capture inherent physical relationships and handle imperfections.
target_description: Target variable representing pressure in bars

name: house_prices
title: House Prices
description: The House Prices dataset comprises 1,460 samples with 81 attributes detailing property features, designed for regression tasks to predict individual house sale prices based on property characteristics.  It is distinct from the Boston and California House Prices datasets.

name: nba_seasons_count
title: NBA Player Seasons Count Dataset
description: This dataset contains comprehensive statistics and information related to NBA players, specifically focusing on their performance during their debut season and its relationship to their subsequent career longevity in the NBA.
target_description: Number of future NBA seasons played by the player after his debut season

name: neural_sim_reg
title: NeuralSimReg Dataset
description: This synthetic dataset represents a regression problem, simulating a scenario where data is generated by an unknown real-world process, represented here by a neural network.

name: sine_waves
title: Sine Waves Regression Dataset
description: This dataset captures time steps from a sine wave to predict subsequent sine values for regression. It includes Gaussian noise, variable intervals between samples, and occasional missing values, making it a complex representation of real-world sequential data scenarios.

name: smoke_test_regression
title: Regression Smoke Test Dataset
description: This smoke test dataset for regression task features a numeric attribute and a categorical attribute, along with intentional missing data, to simply verify model operability without gauging performance.
